    "notes": "Stellar Phase 2 curated 2026-05-30 under curation-data-contract (Tier 1 inversion fix). Radius/Teff/luminosity/mass/age/[Fe/H] all anchored on Tanner et al. 2015 (2015ApJ...800..115T), a dedicated stellar-parameters paper: CHARA interferometry resolved the star (theta_LD 0.674 +/- 0.014 mas -> R 0.9058 +/- 0.0190 Rsun), SED bolometric fit gives L 0.622 +/- 0.014 Lsun and Teff 5394 +/- 62 K (SME spectral Teff 5385 +/- 44 agrees to 9 K), SME spectroscopy gives [Fe/H] -0.04 +/- 0.03 and log g 4.49, Y2 isochrones give mass 0.863 +/- 0.043. No asteroseismology exists for this star. Prior unverified values (Lovis 2006 M 0.86, Rosenthal 2021 R 0.887) superseded by Tanner. [Fe/H] alternatives: Santos 2004 -0.03 +/- 0.04, Sousa 2008 -0.06 +/- 0.02 (all slightly sub-solar). Activity = Gomes da Silva 2021 AMBRE-HARPS log R'HK -4.999 (wmean; -5.013 median, 711 spectra; inactive). AGE IS A DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCE but all methods agree the star is OLD and rule out the youngest (~0.6-2 Gyr, Song 2000) ages: Tanner SME-isochrone 7.5 +/- 3 Gyr (recommended, the more precise of Tanner's two) vs Tanner HRD-isochrone 10.6 +/- 4 vs Mamajek & Hillenbrand 2008 activity/gyrochronology 5.7-6.1 Gyr; ranges overlap ~6-10 Gyr. Tanner notes the old age means the warm asteroid belt cannot be primordial (must be replenished; Beichman 2005). ROTATION: NO measured photometric period exists; only v sin i 0.8 +/- 0.5 km/s (Tanner 2015 SME) and an empirical-relation estimate (~41.7 d, CHES Bao 2024) -- not recorded as a rotation_measurement."
  }
